                           108rb, 109ra, 109rb, 109va, 109vb, 110ra, 110va, 111ra, 111rb, 111va,
                           112ra); inicpit of Text IV and its subsections ( fols. 112rb, 112va,
                           112vb, 113rb, 116va, 117ra, 118rb, 118vb, 119ra); elements of the
                           punctuation signs and Ethiopic numerals; elements of the quire
                           marks.
 
 In the incipit page of Text I (fols. 3r), a few lines
                           are rubricated (alternating with black lines).</seg>
